description:
The Private Life of...

Nature, Science Documentary hosted by Jimmy Doherty, published by BBC in 2010 - English narration


Information
------------------------------

The Private Life of...
Jimmy Doherty investigates the hidden lives of the farmyard animals which are so often taken for granted


3)  Pigs 
There are five and a half million pigs in Britain and we spend, as a nation, Ã‚Â£9 billion a year on pork products. But surely, wonders farmer Jimmy Doherty, there must be more to pigs than their taste. Jimmy visits a farm in Dartmoor to find out about pigs. How sensitive is a pig's nose? Why can they find truffles underground? How do piglets find the right teat to feed from? Pigs are very intelligent, but can they recognise themselves in a mirror? Not only do some pigs have straight tails and stripy fur coats, Jimmy Doherty proves their intelligence in a series of challenges before introducing you to the wild boar, &quot;the SAS of the pig world&quot;. Worth watching purely to see Jimmy learn how to converse in pig, this is probably the only time you will ever see a pig and its &quot;corkscrew todger&quot; work its way towards &quot;what must be the world's longest ejaculation&quot;.

